Danny Ferry has been named the
president and general manager of the  Atlanta Hawks , replacing
Rick Sund.  Ferry, 45, previously worked in the front office for the
Cleveland Cavaliers and San Antonio Spurs.  He averaged seven points over 13 National Basketball
Association seasons and played collegiately at Duke University,
where he earned player of the year honors in 1989.  The Hawks finished last season with 40 wins and 26 losses.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  